HEADWORD: Headborrow
<hw>Head"bor*row</hw> }</mhw>
<pr>(h⟦ecr⟧d"b⟦ucr⟧r*⟦osl⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
chief of a frankpledge, tithing, or decennary, consisting of ten
families; -- called also <altname>borsholder</altname>,
<altname>boroughhead</altname>, <altname>boroughholder</altname>, and
sometimes <altname>tithingman</altname>. See <er>Borsholder</er>.</def>
<mark>[Eng.]</mark> <rj><au>Blackstone.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Modern Law)</fld> <def>A petty constable.</def>
<mark>[Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Head-cheese</ent>⟦br⟧
